  "A factory's average cost per unit is C̄(x) = (5000 + 8x)/x dollars, where x is the number of units produced. What is the average cost per unit when 250 units are produced?": "",
  "$50": "",
  "$28": "",
  "$8": "",
  "$20": "",
  "C̄(250) = (5000 + 8 · 250)/250 = (5000 + 2000)/250 = 7000/250 = $28 per unit.": "",
  "A kayaker paddles upstream against a 2 mph current and then returns downstream. If the kayaker's speed in still water is r mph and the one-way distance is 10 miles, which expression gives the total round-trip time?": "",
  "10r/(r² − 4)": "",
  "20/(r + 2)": "",
  "10/(r − 2) + 10/(r + 2)": "",
  "20/(r − 2)": "",
  "Time = distance/speed. Upstream time = 10/(r − 2), downstream time = 10/(r + 2). Total = 10/(r − 2) + 10/(r + 2).": "",
  "Combine the round-trip time expression 10/(r − 2) + 10/(r + 2) into a single simplified fraction.": "",
  "20/(2r)": "",
  "10r/(r² + 4)": "",
  "20/(r² − 4)": "",
  "20r/(r² − 4)": "",
  "10(r + 2)/[(r − 2)(r + 2)] + 10(r − 2)/[(r − 2)(r + 2)] = (10r + 20 + 10r − 20)/(r² − 4) = 20r/(r² − 4).": "",
  "A biologist models the concentration of a nutrient in a solution as C(t) = 50t/(t² + 25) mg/L, where t is hours after mixing. What is the concentration at t = 5 hours?": "",
  "5 mg/L": "",
  "2 mg/L": "",
  "10 mg/L": "",
  "25 mg/L": "",
  "C(5) = 50(5)/(25 + 25) = 250/50 = 5 mg/L.": "",
  "A company's revenue is R(x) = x(100 − x) and its cost is C(x) = 20x + 500. The profit per unit is P̄(x) = [R(x) − C(x)]/x. Simplify P̄(x).": "",
  "80x − x²": "",
  "100 − 20/x": "",
  "80 − x − 500/x": "",
  "100 − x − 500/x": "",
  "R(x) − C(x) = 100x − x² − 20x − 500 = 80x − x² − 500. Dividing by x: P̄(x) = 80 − x − 500/x.": "",
  "Two printers working together can finish a job in 4 hours. Printer A alone takes 6 hours. Using the equation 1/6 + 1/B = 1/4, how long does Printer B take alone?": "",
  "10 hours": "",
  "8 hours": "",
  "12 hours": "",
  "5 hours": "",
  "1/6 + 1/B = 1/4 → 1/B = 1/4 − 1/6 = 3/12 − 2/12 = 1/12 → B = 12 hours.": "",
  "An electrician uses the parallel resistance formula 1/R_T = 1/R₁ + 1/R₂. Which single simplified fraction equals R_T?": "",
